{"ts": "2026-03-30T19:16:42.684736+00:00", "event_type": "claude", "agent": "Claude", "action": "Bash", "detail": "cd /mnt/data4tb/Warehouse/web3-sdk/dashboard && node -e \"\nconst HEALTH_FIXTURE = \\`# HEALTH.md\n\n## Critical Known Gaps\n\n| ID | Area | Description | Severity | Blocks |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| GAP-001 | Auth | Missing auth implementation | CRITICAL | Phase 6 |\n| GAP-002 | SDK | SDK not fully typed | HIGH | Phase 4 |\n\n## Phase Progress\n\n| Phase | Status | Lead | Blocking |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Phase 1 | Complete | Orchestrator | None |\n| Phase 2 | In Progress | Backend Engineer | Phase 3 |\n\n## Document Freshness\n\n| Document | Last Verified | Threshold | Status | Next Check |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| HEALTH.md | 2026-03-28 | 7 days | ok | 2026-04-04 |\n| DECISIONS.md | 2026-03-20 | 14 days | warn | 2026-04-03 |\n\\`\n\nfunction parseMarkdownTable(content, sectionRegex) {\n  const m = content.match(sectionRegex)\n  if (!m) return []\n  return m[1].trim().split('\\n')\n    .filter(l => l.startsWith('|') && !l.match(/^[\\s|:-]+\\$/))\n    .map(row => row.split('|').map(c => c.trim()).filter(Boolean))\n    .filter(cols => cols.length >= 2)\n}\n\nconst rows = parseMarkdownTable(HEALTH_FIXTURE, /## Critical Known Gaps[\\s\\S]*?\\| ID[^\\n]*\\n\\|[^|]+\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=\\n###|\\n##|\\$)/)\nconsole.log('gaps rows:', rows)\n\"\n", "status": "ok"}
{"ts": "2026-03-30T19:16:54.671926+00:00", "event_type": "claude", "agent": "Claude", "action": "Bash", "detail": "cd /mnt/data4tb/Warehouse/web3-sdk/dashboard && node -e \"\nconst HEALTH_FIXTURE = \\`# HEALTH.md\n\n## Critical Known Gaps\n\n| ID | Area | Description | Severity | Blocks |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| GAP-001 | Auth | Missing auth | CRITICAL | Phase 6 |\n\\`\n\n// Test the regex step by step\nconst m = HEALTH_FIXTURE.match(/## Critical Known Gaps[\\s\\S]*?\\| ID[^\\n]*\\n\\|[^|]+\\n([\\s\\S]*?)(?=\\n###|\\n##|\\$)/)\nconsole.log('match:', m ? m[1] : 'NO MATCH')\n\n// Try simpler\nconst m2 = HEALTH_FIXTURE.match(/## Critical Known Gaps/)\nconsole.log('section found:', !!m2)\n\nconst m3 = HEALTH_FIXTURE.match(/\\| ID/)\nconsole.log('table header found:', !!m3)\n\"\n", "status": "ok"}
